    summary: "Learn to craft prompts that generate compelling blog posts, social media content, email campaigns, and marketing copy that converts.",
    content: `# Prompt Engineering for Content Creation and Marketing\n\nAI-powered content creation is transforming how businesses produce marketing materials. The key to quality output is sophisticated prompt engineering.\n\n## Blog Post Generation\n\n### The Structured Outline Approach\n\`\`\`\nWrite a 1500-word blog post about [topic].\n\nTarget audience: [persona]\nTone: Professional but conversational\nGoal: Drive signups for our free trial\n\nStructure:\n1. Hook with a surprising statistic\n2. Define the problem (200 words)\n3. Present the solution with 3 key points (800 words)\n4. Include a real-world example (300 words)\n5. Call-to-action (200 words)\n\nSEO keywords to include naturally: [keyword1], [keyword2]\n\`\`\`\n\n## Social Media Content\n\n### Platform-Specific Prompts\n\`\`\`\nCreate 5 Twitter/X posts promoting our new AI tool.\n\nConstraints:\n- Under 280 characters each\n- Include 1-2 relevant hashtags\n- Vary the hook: question, statistic, bold claim, story, how-to\n- Conversational tone, no corporate jargon\n- Include a CTA in at least 2 posts\n\`\`\`\n\n## Email Marketing\n\n### The Segmented Approach\n\`\`\`\nWrite 3 versions of this email for different segments:\n1. New subscribers (nurture, educational)\n2. Active users (upsell, feature highlight)\n3. Churned users (win-back, special offer)\n\nProduct: [description]\nKey benefit: [value prop]\nCTA: [desired action]\n\`\`\`\n\n## SEO Content\n\n### The Topic Cluster Strategy\n\`\`\`\nI'm building a content cluster around "[main topic]".\n\nGenerate:\n1. A pillar page outline (3000 words)\n2. 10 supporting article titles targeting long-tail keywords\n3. Internal linking strategy between articles\n4. Meta descriptions for each piece\n\`\`\`\n\n## Content Repurposing\n\n### Multi-Format Prompt\n\`\`\`\nTake this blog post and create:\n1. A LinkedIn post (150 words, professional tone)\n2. A Twitter thread (8 tweets)\n3. An email newsletter summary (200 words)\n4. 5 Instagram caption options (with emoji)\n5. A YouTube video script outline\n\n[paste blog post]\n\`\`\`\n\n## Best Practices\n\n1. **Always specify the audience** — "Marketing managers at B2B SaaS companies" beats "business people"\n2. **Define the voice** — Provide examples of your brand voice\n3. **Set measurable goals** — "Drive clicks" vs "Increase brand awareness" changes the output\n4. **Iterate in stages** — Outline first, then draft, then edit\n5. **Human review is essential** — AI generates, humans curate and refine`,
    image: "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1432888498266-38ffec3eaf0a?w=800",
